font-normal ">The Documents app is a comprehensive document management tool=
 that allows you to automate all of the paperwork necessary for new hires, =
current employees, and terminated employees, review the completion progress=
 for each employee and document, and send new documents or reminders to emp=
loyees.</p><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">You can set up documents you'll ne=
ed employees to sign ahead of time, specify which new hires need to sign wh=
ich documents, and define whether the document requires an e-signature or u=
pload. All paperwork is managed electronically and stored in Rippling for f=
uture reference. Uploaded documents remain within the app until they are ma=
nually deleted by admins.</p><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">The Documents ap=
p is divided into the following tabs: <b>People</b>, <b>Templates</b>, <b>F=
older management</b>, <b>Rules</b>, <b>Bulk upload</b>, and&nbsp;<b>Setting=
s</b>. Learn more about each of these tabs in the sections below.</p><br><a=
 class=3D"absolute opacity-0 scroll-mt-40" id=3D"people-tab" data-id=3D"hat=
_people-tab"></a><h2 class=3D"text-4xl font-bold" id=3D"people-tab" data-id=
=3D"people-tab">People tab</h2><a class=3D"absolute mt-20 opacity-0" id=3D"=
people-tab" data-id=3D"hab_people-tab"></a><br><p class=3D"font-normal ">On=
 the People tab, you'll find a list of all of your employees, including act=
ive employees and candidates who have accepted offers, along with the numbe=
r of documents and notices they've received and completed.</p><br><p class=
=3D"font-normal ">From each employee row, you can resend a document or a re=
minder to the employee, upload a missing document, or dive into the employe=
e's document history.</p><br><img class=3D"shadow-md border border-opacity-=
